Dialogue: 0,1:44:31.00,1:44:35.00,ZHU,,0,0,0,,梅根 · 希普韋爾\N{\fs50}1990 — 2016
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.50,0:01:07.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我丈夫曾跟我說過，我的想像力過於活躍{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}My husband used to tell me I have an overactive imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.66,0:01:09.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我情不自禁{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I can't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.90,0:01:12.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}比如說，你有沒有坐在火車上{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I mean, haven't you ever been on a train
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.39,0:01:15.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}對住在軌道兩旁的人們的生活感到好奇？{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}and wondered about the lives of the people who live near the tracks?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:17.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那種你不可能經歷的生活{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}The lives you've never lived.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.24,0:01:21.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,這些就是我想知道的事{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}These are things I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.69,0:01:27.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一天兩次，我坐在前面第三節車廂{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Twice a day I sit in the third car from the front
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.50,0:01:30.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在那裏我可以清楚地看到我最喜歡的房子{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}where I have the perfect view into my favorite house:
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.36,0:01:32.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}貝克特路十五號…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Number 15 Beckett Road...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.82,0:01:42.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不知道確切是那一天{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I don't know when exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.74,0:01:46.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想大約在一年以前我開始注意到她{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I suppose I started noticing her about a year ago
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.05,0:01:49.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}幾個月過去以後{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}and, gradually, as the months went past,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.24,0:01:51.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她漸漸變得對我重要起來…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}she became important to me...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.29,0:02:13.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不再是從前的那個女孩{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I'm not the girl I used to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.49,0:02:16.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}這個我想人們可以從我臉上看出來{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I think people can see it on my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.99,0:02:35.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她就是我之所失{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}She's what I lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.43,0:02:39.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她就是我之所欲…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}She's everything I want to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.68,0:03:17.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想像她是個畫家…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I imagine she's a painter...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.71,0:03:24.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}富有創造力；而他是醫生或建築師{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}She's creative. He's a doctor or an architect.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.29,0:03:32.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}他笑聲爽朗{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}He has a good laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.66,0:03:34.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她不會做飯{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}She can't cook.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.66,0:03:42.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想知道每晚入睡前他們互相會說什麼話{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I wonder what they say to each other before they go to sleep.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.58,0:03:55.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}今天她的名字是傑絲，明天就可以是莉莎或安柏{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Today her name is Jess, tomorrow it could be Lisa or Amber.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.21,0:03:58.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}這全取決於當天的情況，取決於我的心情{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}It all depends on the day, it depends on my mood.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.30,0:04:04.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}事實是：我不知道她的名字{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}The truth is, I don't know her name.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.14,0:04:09.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不知道她是否是畫家，或他是否笑聲爽朗{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I don't know if she paints or whether he has a good laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.96,0:04:13.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我只知道他們知道愛…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I just know they know love...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.86,0:04:18.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有時我會出神地努力回憶…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Sometimes I catch myself trying to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.50,0:04:22.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}…我最後一次與另一個人的真正意義上的接觸…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}the last time I had meaningful contact with another person...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.11,0:04:34.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我曾經住在兩個門牌號之後——貝克特路十三號{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I used to live two doors down... number 13 Beckett Road.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.62,0:04:38.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}那是我的第一個家{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}It was my first home.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.98,0:04:42.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我們一起買的，那是我們的家{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}We bought it together. It was ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.76,0:04:49.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}每天，我都告誡自己別去看{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Every day, I tell myself not to look.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.75,0:04:54.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但我仍然會看…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}But then I look...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.30,0:05:05.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你一個人嗎？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- Are you alone?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.08,0:05:07.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,沒事，來吧，隨便坐\N{\rENG}No, come. It's all yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.52,0:05:14.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你的寶貝好可愛，嗨，寶貝  - 謝謝\N{\rENG}- Your baby's so cute. Hi, baby.  - Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.55,0:05:16.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 他是…他是男孩？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- Is it... Is it a boy?  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.76,0:05:19.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,太可愛了，他…他多大了？\N{\rENG}So sweet. How... how old is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.90,0:05:22.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 六個月  - 六個月\N{\rENG}- Six months.  - Six months.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.16,0:05:26.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,好可愛啊\N{\rENG}So sweet.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.45,0:06:11.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有位老師曾對我說，我是自我重塑的情婦{\i1}\N{\rENG\i1}A teacher once told me I was a mistress of self-reinvention...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.27,0:06:18.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}當時我不太確定這話是什麼意思{\i1}\N{\rENG\i1}I wasn't really sure what it meant at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.28,0:06:23.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但自從搬到這裏，我開始慢慢理解了…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}But since moving here I've come to understand it...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.45,0:06:25.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\rZHU}{\fs60\fsp20\pos(980,600)}六個月以前
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.54,0:06:31.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}哈德遜河畔阿茲利的生活平淡又無聊{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Ardsley-on-Hudson is boring and routine.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.45,0:06:35.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}這裏簡直就是個嬰兒工廠{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}It's a fucking baby factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.76,0:06:39.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我想重新開啟我的生活{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I want to start my life over again.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.48,0:06:44.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}到目前為止，我當過叛逆青少年{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}So far, I've been: rebellious teenager,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.98,0:06:48.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}情侶{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}lover,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.23,0:06:50.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}女侍者{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}waitress...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.04,0:06:52.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}畫廊主管{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}gallery director,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.66,0:06:56.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}保姆{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}nanny,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.19,0:07:00.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}還有賤貨{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}and a whore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.74,0:07:05.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}不一定是按照這個次序{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}And not necessarily in that order.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:11.19,0:07:13.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我再也成為不了好妻子{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I can't just be a wife anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.59,0:07:19.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}這就是為什麼我會徹夜不眠，盯著天花板{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}That's why I stay awake at night, staring at the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.95,0:07:25.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,事實上只有在我跑步時，我才覺得是我自己\N{\rENG}In fact, the only time I feel like myself is when I'm running.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.35,0:07:29.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,你一直有這樣的感覺嗎？\N{\rENG}You always felt that way?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.09,0:07:36.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,也許從大概十七歲起\N{\rENG}Maybe since I was about seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.53,0:07:39.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,和麥克在一起時\N{\rENG}With Mac.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.49,0:07:41.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,麥克？麥克是誰？\N{\rENG}Mac? Who's Mac?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.17,0:07:45.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我哥哥最好的朋友\N{\rENG}My brother's best friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.54,0:07:48.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,那時我哥哥剛死…\N{\rENG}My brother who died...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.58,0:07:58.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,緊張時我容易微笑\N{\rENG}I tend to smile when I'm nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.23,0:08:00.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,有時我會發笑\N{\rENG}Sometimes, I laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.23,0:08:14.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,有一年時間，麥克和我住在一間狩獵小木屋裏\N{\rENG}For a year, Mac and I lived in this hunting cabin.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.56,0:08:18.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我們瘋狂做愛\N{\rENG}We started fucking.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.37,0:08:27.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我們是世界上最傷心的人\N{\rENG}We were the saddest people we knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.94,0:08:32.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,但從某種意義上說，那個木屋使我們幸福\N{\rENG}But in a way, that cabin made us happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.76,0:08:36.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,沒人能夠找到我們\N{\rENG}No one could find us.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.85,0:08:39.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,每個人都以為我們死了\N{\rENG}Everyone thought we were dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.99,0:08:43.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,假設今天你想逃跑，就在現在，你會去哪裏？\N{\rENG}And if you were to run away today, right now, where would you go?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.94,0:09:00.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,我曾讀到過如果被火車撞到，你的衣服會被火車撕掉\N{\rENG}I read once that when a train hits, it can rip the clothes right off of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.15,0:09:13.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我非常確定斯科特認為保姆工作能使我不那麼焦躁\N{\rENG}I'm pretty sure Scott thinks the nanny job is gonna make me less restless,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.81,0:09:17.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,能使我想要懷孕…\N{\rENG}make me wanna get pregnant...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.47,0:09:19.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,但情況並非如此？\N{\rENG}And that's not the case?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.02,0:09:23.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,每天晚上做完工，我都跑著回家\N{\rENG}When I finish work, every night I run home,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.45,0:09:27.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我站在淋浴下盡快洗掉我身上的嬰兒味道\N{\rENG}and I get in the shower and wash the smell of that baby off me as fast as I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.31,0:09:45.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,今天早晨你醒來時，我過去把你抱過來和我躺在一起\N{\rENG}When you woke up this morning I went and I brought you back to bed with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.20,0:09:50.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,在我給你餵奶時，我們聽見爹地在廚房唱歌，是不是？\N{\rENG}And when I was feeding you, we heard daddy singing from the kitchen, didn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.78,0:09:57.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}「祝你生日快樂，祝你生日快樂{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Happy Birthday to you, Happy Birthday to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.38,0:10:03.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}「祝你生日快樂，親愛的安娜，祝你生日快樂！」{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Happy Birthday dear Anna, Happy Birthday to you!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.43,0:10:08.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,爹地走上樓，端來一頓豐盛的早餐\N{\rENG}Daddy came upstairs with a beautiful breakfast
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.36,0:10:10.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是他給媽咪做的，是嗎？\N{\rENG}that he made for Mommy, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.56,0:10:12.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，沒錯\N{\rENG}Yes he did.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.97,0:10:14.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,謝謝，梅根\N{\rENG}Thank you, Megan.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.68,0:10:20.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,好了\N{\rENG}There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.82,0:10:30.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,噢，你好啊\N{\rENG}Oh, hello.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.29,0:10:37.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,我發誓，有的時候我感覺我的心都快要爆炸了\N{\rENG}I swear I sometimes feel like my heart is gonna explode.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.46,0:10:39.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是說，看看她\N{\rENG}I mean, look at her.
