Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.10,0:26:00.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}天哪，蕾切爾！你這人他媽的怎麼回事？{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Jesus Christ, Rachel! What the hell is wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.30,0:26:05.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我花了一個小時開著車一直在找你！{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I've spent the past hour driving around looking for you!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.69,0:26:09.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你他媽的把安娜嚇個半死，你知道嗎？{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}You scared the shit out of Anna, do you know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.14,0:26:15.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她以為你想要…她都想打電話報警了{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}She thought you were going to... She wanted to call the police.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:15.45,0:26:16.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}所以…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}So just...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.73,0:26:21.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}別來打攪我們！{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Leave us alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.29,0:26:26.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你盡可以毀掉你自己的生活，但絕不允許你破壞我們的{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}You can ruin your own life if you want to, but you're not gonna destroy ours.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.93,0:26:28.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不會再保護你了{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I'm not gonna protect you any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.96,0:26:34.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,噢，我的天哪…\N{\rENG}Oh my god...
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.39,0:26:56.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,蕾切爾，把門開開\N{\rENG}Rachel, open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.31,0:27:02.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 凱茜，我現在需要點時間  - 你沒事吧？蕾切爾，快開門\N{\rENG}- Cathy, I just need a sec.  - Are you ok? Rachel, open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.16,0:27:06.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,我得了病毒性腸胃炎\N{\rENG}I have a stomach flu, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.19,0:27:09.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,你沒得腸胃炎，這他媽怎麼回事，蕾切爾？\N{\rENG}You don't have a flu. What the fuck, Rachel?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.63,0:27:11.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不是傻…\N{\rENG}I'm not stupid...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.34,0:27:14.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 蕾切爾！ - 凱茜，你走吧！\N{\rENG}- Rachel!  - Cathy, just go away!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.29,0:27:26.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}過來一下，就一下{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Come here for one second.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:28.48,0:27:31.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,- {\i1}說「操你媽，安娜 · 博伊德」{\i0}  - {\i1}操你媽，安娜 · 博伊德！{\i0}\N{\rENG}- Say "fuck you, Anna Boyd."  - Fuck you, Anna Boyd!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.39,0:27:41.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,你個賤貨！\N{\rENG}You whore!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.30,0:28:47.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,有誰想分享一下自己的戒酒天數嗎？三個月內的？\N{\rENG}Anyone counting days one to ninety who would like to share a day count?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.67,0:28:49.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,嘿，我叫詹森，我是個酒鬼\N{\rENG}Hey, I'm Jason, I'm an alcoholic.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.59,0:28:52.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 歡迎，詹森  - 我已經二十二天沒碰了\N{\rENG}- Welcome, Jason.  - I've got twenty-two days back.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.89,0:28:57.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,還有嗎？\N{\rENG}Anyone else?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.29,0:29:07.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 嗨，我叫蕾切爾…  - 歡迎，蕾切爾\N{\rENG}- Hi, I'm Rachel, and...  - Welcome, Rachel.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.71,0:29:11.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,今天是第一天，我想\N{\rENG}This is day one, I suppose.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.42,0:29:31.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,我來這裏是因為我…\N{\rENG}I'm here because I...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.00,0:29:33.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,因為我…\N{\rENG}Because I...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.00,0:29:38.16,CHS,,0,0,0,,因為我醒來時渾身是血\N{\rENG}Because I woke up covered in blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.97,0:29:43.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,我的胳膊滿是瘀傷…\N{\rENG}And I had bruises all over my arm and...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.89,0:29:50.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,通常這是由於我摔跤導致的，還經常有人扶我起來\N{\rENG}It's usually from when I've fallen and someone has helped me up.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.53,0:29:54.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,我丈夫…\N{\rENG}My husband...
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.00,0:29:58.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,他常常告訴我前一天晚上我的行為\N{\rENG}He used to tell me what I'd done the night before.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.97,0:30:06.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道像那樣子醒過來，你只會說你很抱歉\N{\rENG}And I learned that when you wake up like that, you just say you're sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.15,0:30:11.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,你只會為你的所作所為而道歉\N{\rENG}You just say you're sorry for what you did
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.81,0:30:16.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,為你成為這樣的人而道歉，並保證再也不會這麼做\N{\rENG}and you're sorry for who you are and you're never gonna do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.59,0:30:18.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是你會的，還是會這麼做\N{\rENG}But you do. You do it again.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.40,0:30:23.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,有些時間…不見了\N{\rENG}And there's... time missing.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.53,0:30:26.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,我需要回憶\N{\rENG}I need to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.74,0:30:30.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,我需要回憶\N{\rENG}I need to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.29,0:30:34.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,好的，謝謝你，蕾切爾\N{\rENG}Okay. Thank you, Rachel.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.98,0:30:55.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,那跟無家可歸者有關，我不記得叫什麼名字了\N{\rENG}It was that homeless thing. I don't remember what it was called.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.25,0:30:56.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 對了，「安全庇護所」…  - 是的\N{\rENG}- Oh, Safe Shelter...  - Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.77,0:30:59.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那是件筒式抹胸，對嗎？ - 是的，沒錯\N{\rENG}- That was a tube top, right?  - Yeah, it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.90,0:31:10.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你喜歡吃惡魔的蛋嗎，瑪莎？ - 惡魔蛋？是的，喜歡\N{\rENG}- Do you like Devil's Eggs, Martha?  - Deviled Eggs? Yeah, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.33,0:31:12.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\rZHU\fs50}一種抹了芥末等調料的煮蛋\N{\rCHS}惡魔蛋\N{\rENG}Deviled Eggs.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.08,0:31:15.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,經典款\N{\rENG}The classics.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.75,0:31:16.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,有誰想嘗一個嗎？\N{\rENG}Do you want to try one, anybody?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:16.89,0:31:18.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,這個放到外面去，我不想把蛋和甜點放在一起\N{\rENG}Those go outside. I don't want the eggs with the dessert.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.91,0:31:21.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,放哪兒都他媽一樣，行嗎？你想把它們放這兒？\N{\rENG}It doesn't fucking matter where they go, okay? So do you want to put them here?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.64,0:31:25.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,你想把它們和你的熱狗放一起？還是想拿幾個和你的奎奴亞藜放一起？\N{\rENG}Do you want them with your hot dogs? Or you can put a couple with your quinoa if you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.55,0:31:29.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,或者你想把它們和你的色拉和玉米放一起，還放兩個到牆上！\N{\rENG}Or do you want to put them with your other salad and your corn, and a couple on the wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.84,0:31:32.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 蕾切爾！ - 我沒事，湯姆，住手！\N{\rENG}- Rachel!  - I'm fine, Tom. Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.37,0:31:35.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不支持我，你從沒支持過我\N{\rENG}You didn't back me up. You never have my back.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.64,0:31:38.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你從沒支持過我  - 那是我老闆的老婆\N{\rENG}- You never have my back.  - That's my boss's wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.33,0:31:42.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你那樣很可能會讓我丟飯碗的  - 我才他媽不管呢，我是你老婆\N{\rENG}- You probably got me fired back there.  - I don't give a fuck. I'm your wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.78,0:31:44.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我是你老婆你卻從不…  - 蕾切爾！\N{\rENG}- I'm your wife and you never...  - Rachel!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.41,0:31:45.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,你卻從不他媽的支持我！\N{\rENG}You never fucking support me!
Dialogue: 0,0:31:45.92,0:31:49.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,求你別鬧了！嘿，別這樣，我需要你現在醒一醒\N{\rENG}Please stop. Hey, come on. I need you to focus here.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.81,0:31:52.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 別他媽的那樣對我說話！ - 放鬆！\N{\rENG}- Don't fucking talk to me like that!  - Relax!
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.40,0:32:09.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 蕾切爾，你回來了  - 凱茜，對不起了\N{\rENG}- Rachel, there you are.  - Cathy, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.43,0:32:11.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我需要把我東西規整一下，我…\N{\rENG}I need to get my shit together. I'm...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.74,0:32:15.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,你一定是沃森小姐，我是萊利警探\N{\rENG}You must be Miss Watson. I'm Detective Riley.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.81,0:32:19.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,這位是加斯基爾警探，我們需要問你幾個問題\N{\rENG}This is Detective Gaskill. We need to ask you a few questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.80,0:32:22.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 和什麼有關？ - 能坐下麼？\N{\rENG}- What's this about?  - Want to sit down?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.91,0:32:31.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,你能告訴我星期五晚上你在哪裏？\N{\rENG}Can you tell me where you were Friday night?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.38,0:32:38.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,我…我先在城裏工作，然後…\N{\rENG}I was at work in the city. And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.15,0:32:45.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 然後我去看望我丈夫了  - 你的意思是你前夫？\N{\rENG}- And then I went to visit my husband.  - You mean your EX-husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.84,0:32:51.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，所以我在哈德遜河畔阿茲利下了火車，然後…\N{\rENG}Yes. So I got off the train at Ardsley-on-Hudson. And then...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.48,0:32:54.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,然後我覺得這是個壞主意\N{\rENG}And then I decided that it was a bad idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.03,0:32:57.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,大概是什麼時候你得到這樣的結論的？\N{\rENG}Around what time did you reach that conclusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.09,0:33:00.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,我回到這裏是十一點鐘\N{\rENG}I was back here by 11:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.32,0:33:03.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的，是的\N{\rENG}Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.91,0:33:07.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,你回這裏的路上，有沒有在任何地方逗留？\N{\rENG}On your way back here, did you stop anywhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.30,0:33:08.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,沒有\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.90,0:33:11.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,你幾點在那兒坐的火車？\N{\rENG}And what time did you take the train there?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.64,0:33:15.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 呃，六點  - 那麼…那幾個小時…\N{\rENG}- Um, 6:00.  - So... What did you do
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.37,0:33:19.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,…你在阿茲利幹什麼呢，如果你沒去看你的前夫？\N{\rENG}during those hours in Ardsley if you weren't seeing your ex-husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.55,0:33:29.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,記不記得見過這個女人？\N{\rENG}Do you remember seeing this woman?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.50,0:33:32.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,她為你前夫工作\N{\rENG}She worked for your ex-husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.30,0:33:36.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 她失蹤了  - 你什麼意思，她失蹤了？\N{\rENG}- She's gone missing.  - What do you mean she's missing?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.42,0:33:39.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,她丈夫說她再也沒有回家，就是在你在…\N{\rENG}Her husband said she never came back home the same night
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.29,0:33:42.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,…哈德遜河畔阿茲利下火車的同一天晚上\N{\rENG}you got off the train in Ardsley-on-Hudson.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.42,0:33:46.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我只是…我…  - 你認識梅根 · 希普韋爾嗎？\N{\rENG}- I was just...I was...  - Do you know Megan Hipwell?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.08,0:33:47.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 不  - 你見過她嗎？\N{\rENG}- No.  - Did you see her?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.77,0:33:52.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 沒有，我想我沒見過  - 是因為你處於醉酒狀態？\N{\rENG}- No. I don't think so.  - Is that because you were inebriated?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.89,0:33:55.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,只是想澄清一下，你說你星期五去工作了？\N{\rENG}Just to clarify, you said you were at work Friday?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.58,0:33:59.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是指你在公共關係部的那份工作嗎？\N{\rENG}Are you referring to your job in Public Relations?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.24,0:34:00.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.11,0:34:02.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,可是據我瞭解，一年多前你就從那兒被解雇了\N{\rENG}It's my understanding you were fired from that job over a year ago
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.87,0:34:05.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,因為你的酗酒問題？\N{\rENG}because of your drinking problem?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.50,0:34:20.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，今天就到這兒吧\N{\rENG}Ok. That's enough for now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.29,0:34:27.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你想起些什麼了，給我們打電話\N{\rENG}If you're able to remember anything else, give us a call.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.00,0:34:32.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,你真的被解雇了嗎？\N{\rENG}Did you really get fired?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.12,0:34:34.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看，我是不想讓你擔心我付不起房租…\N{\rENG}Look, I didn't want you to worry that I couldn't pay the rent...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.86,0:34:38.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,既然你沒了工作，那你整天都在幹什麼？\N{\rENG}If you don't have a job, then what do you do everyday?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.26,0:34:39.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,我…\N{\rENG}I...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.37,0:34:43.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我…我坐火車  - 你什麼？\N{\rENG}- I ride the train.  - You what?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.28,0:34:46.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,我坐火車上紐約再坐回來\N{\rENG}I ride the train to New York and back.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.39,0:34:51.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,你的贍養費都用在這上面了？買哪兒都不去的車票？\N{\rENG}That's what your alimony's paying for? Tickets to nowhere?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.19,0:34:56.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 這真他媽的怪異，蕾切爾！ - 行了，行了\N{\rENG}- That's really fucking weird, Rachel!  - Okay. Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.42,0:35:01.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,我…我上了火車\N{\rENG}I got on the train.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.75,0:35:07.21,CHS,,0,0,0,,然後，我…我下了火車，我不知道！一切都太模糊了…\N{\rENG}And then, I got off the train. I don't know! It's very unclear...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.25,0:35:09.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,你什麼都不記得了，是嗎？\N{\rENG}You don't remember anything, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.16,0:35:15.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,你知道，我讀到過在長島有個男的，他糊塗了\N{\rENG}You know, I read about this man in Long Island who blacked out.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.73,0:35:18.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,他離開酒吧，開車回到…\N{\rENG}He left a bar and drove to the house
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.64,0:35:22.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,…他從小長大的房子，把裏面的住戶一個個扎死\N{\rENG}that he'd grown up in, stabbed its occupants to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.59,0:35:25.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,他第二天早上醒來，對所做的事全然不知\N{\rENG}He woke up the next morning oblivious to what he did
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.30,0:35:27.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,直到警察來把他抓走…\N{\rENG}until the police came to get him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.41,0:35:28.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 蕾切爾！ - 什麼？什麼？\N{\rENG}- Rachel!  - What? What?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.00,0:35:31.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,你必須搬走，我不能再這樣做了\N{\rENG}You have to leave. I can't do this anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.00,0:35:33.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我會給你幾周時間  - 等一下\N{\rENG}- I'll give you a few weeks.  - Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.37,0:35:35.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,等一下\N{\rENG}Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.29,0:35:40.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 萊利警探！萊利警探！ - 是的，我同意你說的，可是…\N{\rENG}- Detective Riley! Detective Riley!  - Yeah, I agree with you, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.02,0:35:45.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,我見到有人和梅根 · 希普韋爾在一起，不過不是在週五晚上\N{\rENG}I saw someone with Megan Hipwell, but not on Friday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.58,0:35:49.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,她…她有了婚外情，她有一個情人\N{\rENG}She was having an affair. She had a lover.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.58,0:35:52.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我就是想告訴你這個  - 我還以為你不認識她呢\N{\rENG}- That's what I'm trying to tell you.  - I thought you didn't know her.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.56,0:35:55.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是的，但是我看見她了  - 你在哪兒看見的？\N{\rENG}- No. But I saw her.  - You saw her where?
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.10,0:35:58.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,我…我從火車上看見她，她站在平台上，和那個男人\N{\rENG}I saw her from the train. She was standing on the deck with this man.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.59,0:36:01.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 和他丈夫，斯科特 · 希普韋爾？ - 不是，那不是她丈夫\N{\rENG}- With her husband, Scott Hipwell?  - No. It wasn't him.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.64,0:36:05.18,CHS,,0,0,0,,那個男人不一樣，他們吻在了一起\N{\rENG}This man was different. And they were kissing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.56,0:36:08.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,哇哦，這相當地巧啊，不是麼？\N{\rENG}Wow. That's pretty coincidental, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.96,0:36:12.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,你碰巧在一列火車上，它在一個你不認識但不知怎麼…\N{\rENG}You just happen to be on a train at the same exact moment that a woman you don't know,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.69,0:36:14.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,…又能認出的女人正在出軌的那一刻恰好經過？\N{\rENG}but somehow recognize, is cheating on her husband?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.99,0:36:18.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我知道這聽起來很荒唐，可…  - 鄰居們星期五晚上…\N{\rENG}- I know it sounds crazy, but...  - Neighbors saw a drunk woman
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.18,0:36:21.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,…在她家附近見到過一個醉醺醺的女人\N{\rENG}in the vicinity of her house Friday night.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.01,0:36:26.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,梅根 · 希普韋爾的確和安娜 · 沃森有點像\N{\rENG}Megan Hipwell does bear a resemblance to Anna Watson.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.63,0:36:30.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,沃森太太報告說有時你會未獲邀請地去他們家\N{\rENG}Mrs. Watson reported that you go to their house sometimes uninvited.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.50,0:36:34.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,甚至有一次，你闖進去抱走了他們的孩子\N{\rENG}And that on one occasion, you actually broke in and took their child.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.37,0:36:37.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,我給你來點忠告吧\N{\rENG}Let me give you some advice.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.23,0:36:42.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,別再回貝克特路，別再聯繫你的前夫\N{\rENG}Don't go back to Beckett Road. Don't contact your ex-husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.39,0:36:45.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,別再去任何跟安娜 · 沃森或她的寶貝很近的地方\N{\rENG}Don't go anywhere near Anna Watson or her baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.42,0:36:47.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你在聽我說嗎？ - 是的\N{\rENG}- Are you listening to me?  - Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.62,0:36:51.22,CHS,,0,0,0,,你已經不再在那裏生活了\N{\rENG}You don't live there anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.77,0:36:53.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,離遠點\N{\rENG}Stay away.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.60,0:37:04.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}你知道，我總是撒謊{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}You know, I lie all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.69,0:37:07.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\rZHU}{\fs60\fsp20\pos(980,600)}四個月以前
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.06,0:37:11.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,我對斯科特撒謊，我對你撒謊\N{\rENG}I lie to Scott. I lie to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.04,0:37:17.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道這不是心理治療的關注點，但是…\N{\rENG}I mean I know that's not the point of therapy, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.80,0:37:20.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,我必須保持事物的模糊性\N{\rENG}I have to keep things vague.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.91,0:37:25.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,把所有男人都混起來，所有的前任、情人\N{\rENG}Jumble up all the men, the Exes, the lovers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.60,0:37:32.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,不管他們是誰，不管他們給我怎樣的感覺\N{\rENG}It doesn't matter who they are. It matters how they make me feel.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.29,0:37:42.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,撒謊就像是做一次旅行\N{\rENG}Lying is like taking a trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.15,0:37:51.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像是有了一個秘密\N{\rENG}It's like having a secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.21,0:37:56.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,就像是觸摸你自己而沒有任何人知道…\N{\rENG}It's like touching yourself and no one else knows...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.50,0:38:06.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,除了你自己\N{\rENG}Except you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:06.85,0:38:09.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是你只是在假裝\N{\rENG}But you're just pretending.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.81,0:38:15.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,你只是在假裝觸摸你自己\N{\rENG}You're just pretending to touch yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.29,0:38:28.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,斯科特佔有慾很強，容易妒忌\N{\rENG}Scott's possessive. Jealous.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:31.10,0:38:33.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,他喜歡擁有我\N{\rENG}He likes to own me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.72,0:38:38.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,他破解了我所有的密碼\N{\rENG}He figures out all my passwords.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.43,0:38:43.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,這倒是有點性感\N{\rENG}Which is kinda sexy.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.85,0:38:56.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以當我昨晚回家時，斯科特正在我筆記本電腦上好奇地…\N{\rENG}So, when I came home last night, Scott was on my laptop wondering why...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.44,0:38:58.85,CHS,,0,0,0,,斯科特的行為是不正常的\N{\rENG}Scott's behavior is not normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.41,0:39:02.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,這是感情虐待的一種形式\N{\rENG}It's a form of emotional abuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.93,0:39:07.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,你害怕過斯科特嗎？\N{\rENG}Are you ever afraid of Scott?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.10,0:39:11.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,這不是虐待\N{\rENG}It's not abuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:11.96,0:39:14.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,不在乎的話就不是虐待，我不在乎\N{\rENG}Not if you don't care. And I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.79,0:39:17.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,也許對你來說，這變成了一種正常態\N{\rENG}Maybe it's become a normal state for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.30,0:39:23.56,CHS,,0,0,0,,我總是在想著你，這正常嗎？\N{\rENG}Is it normal I think about you all the time?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.94,0:39:34.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}幾乎正好一周以前{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Almost exactly a week ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.84,0:39:39.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}梅根 · 希普韋爾走出貝克特路十五號後就消失了{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Megan Hipwell walked out of Number 15 Beckett Road and disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.16,0:39:42.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}再也沒人看見過她，她的電話和銀行卡週五以後…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}No one has seen her since. Neither her phone nor her bank cards
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.54,0:39:44.83,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}…也再沒有使用過{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}have been used since Friday.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.66,0:39:59.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}一個很棒的女人，雖然個性內斂卻有顆溫暖的心{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}A wonderful woman. An intensely private person with a warm heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.58,0:40:01.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}在她十六歲時，她失去了哥哥{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}She lost a brother when she was sixteen,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:01.78,0:40:05.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}她的父母也在幾年前雙雙過世{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}and both her parents died a few years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.45,0:40:12.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}斯科特 · 希普韋爾盼望出現任何能提供她消息的人{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Scott Hipwell urges anyone with information to please come forward.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.92,0:40:30.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你是梅根的朋友？ - 是的，我叫蕾切爾\N{\rENG}- You're Megan's friend?  - Yes. Rachel.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.41,0:40:31.94,CHS,,0,0,0,,進來吧\N{\rENG}Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.15,0:40:38.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 想來杯咖啡嗎？ - 好的，謝謝\N{\rENG}- Do you want a coffee?  - Sure. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.82,0:40:45.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,不好意思，亂的很\N{\rENG}Sorry it's a mess.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.57,0:40:49.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,我在找她的身份證和出生證\N{\rENG}I've been hunting for her social, birth certificate.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:49.67,0:40:51.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,警察什麼都需要\N{\rENG}The cops need a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.52,0:40:57.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我們以前見過面嗎？ - 我…我想沒見過\N{\rENG}- Have we met somewhere before?  - I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.10,0:41:01.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 那你怎麼認識梅根的？ - 呃…通過畫廊\N{\rENG}- And you know Megan from?  - From the gallery.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.37,0:41:05.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你是藝術家？ - 唔，我想算是吧\N{\rENG}- Are you an artist?  - Well, I like to think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.83,0:41:14.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,你在電話裏說你想告訴我有關梅根的一些事\N{\rENG}So you said on the phone, you wanted to tell me something about Megan.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.67,0:41:18.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,你想告訴我什麼？\N{\rENG}What did you want to tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:20.34,0:41:26.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,星期五上午，我看見你妻子和一個人在一起\N{\rENG}I saw your wife with someone, on Friday morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.34,0:41:27.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,和誰？\N{\rENG}With who?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.20,0:41:31.23,CHS,,0,0,0,,她站在你們的平台上面\N{\rENG}She was up there on your porch.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.05,0:41:36.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是從火車上看見的，因為每天我都坐車去曼哈頓\N{\rENG}I saw her from the train because I commute to Manhattan everyday
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.68,0:41:39.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,我正好經過這裏\N{\rENG}and I go straight past here.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.37,0:41:47.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,她吻了他\N{\rENG}She kissed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.17,0:41:50.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,他們在親吻\N{\rENG}They were kissing.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.47,0:41:58.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我很抱歉，我知道聽到這樣的事真的很可怕\N{\rENG}I'm sorry. I know this is a terrible thing to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.15,0:42:06.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道這是什麼感覺\N{\rENG}I know how it feels.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.21,0:42:11.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,他長什麼樣？\N{\rENG}What did he look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.30,0:42:17.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,他…他有平均的身高\N{\rENG}He was average height.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.77,0:42:19.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,他是黑色頭髮\N{\rENG}He had dark hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:20.51,0:42:22.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,他們在外面的平台上？\N{\rENG}And they were out there on the porch?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.76,0:42:24.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.43,0:42:32.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,操！\N{\rENG}Fuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:39.77,0:42:41.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,操！\N{\rENG}Fuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.23,0:42:48.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,噢，不，不，不，謝謝\N{\rENG}No, no, no. Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.83,0:42:53.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,好吧，當然\N{\rENG}OK. Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.91,0:43:02.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,可能吧，我不知道，也許這樣反而倒好？\N{\rENG}It could, I don't know. Maybe it's a good thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.38,0:43:05.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,這樣可能意味著她沒事\N{\rENG}It could mean she's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.12,0:43:09.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 她只是跟著別人跑了  - 是的\N{\rENG}- She just ran off with someone.  - Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.90,0:43:22.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 她跟你談過嗎？ - 噢，不，我沒聽到過任何事\N{\rENG}- She talked to you?  - Oh no. I haven't heard anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.65,0:43:24.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,你跟她足夠熟悉，都知道我們住的地方\N{\rENG}You know her well enough to know where we live.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:24.95,0:43:26.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,梅根沒有太多朋友\N{\rENG}Megan doesn't have many friends.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.59,0:43:33.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,唔，我曾在附近居住過…她和我，我們學過瑜伽…\N{\rENG}Well, I used to live nearby... She and I, we took yoga...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.81,0:43:35.89,CHS,,0,0,0,,我們一起學過普拉提課\N{\rENG}We took pilates together.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.92,0:43:39.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想我該走了，我覺得我已經佔用你太多時間了\N{\rENG}I think I should go, I feel like I've taken up too much of your time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.25,0:43:46.28,CHS,,0,0,0,,非常抱歉要以這樣的方式告訴你這事\N{\rENG}So sorry to have had to tell you that in that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.72,0:43:50.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,你覺得你能認出他來嗎？如果你見到他？\N{\rENG}Do you think you'd recognize him again? If you saw him?
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.14,0:43:52.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\rENG}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:53.43,0:43:55.88,CHS,,0,0,0,,有個傢伙，心理醫生\N{\rENG}There was a guy, a therapist.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.20,0:44:01.09,CHS,,0,0,0,,他的名字叫阿布迪克…阿布迪克\N{\rENG}His name's Abdic. Abdic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.42,0:44:05.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,卡馬爾 · 阿布迪克\N{\rENG}Kamal Abdic.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.70,0:44:12.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看到的是他嗎？\N{\rENG}Is that who you saw?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.91,0:44:16.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道，真的說不好\N{\rENG}I don't know. I really can't tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.91,0:44:20.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,她他媽的花很多時間和她心理醫生在一起\N{\rENG}She spends a lot of fucking time with her shrink.
