Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.32,0:46:41.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,不\N{\rENG}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.37,0:46:43.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,梅根\N{\rENG}Megan.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.46,0:46:48.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,別讓事情一發不可收拾，我們再也不能合作\N{\rENG}Don't make it impossible for us to work together.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.16,0:46:57.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,梅根，我可能會被吊銷執照的\N{\rENG}Megan, I could lose my practice.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.65,0:47:04.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,我才他媽不管！我才他媽不管你的什麼狗屁執照！\N{\rENG}I don't give a fuck. I don't give a fuck about your fucking practice!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.67,0:47:07.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,我才他媽不管…\N{\rENG}I don't give a fuck...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.82,0:47:24.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}卡馬爾 · 阿布迪克醫生被帶走詢問有關哈德遜河畔阿茲利…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Dr. Kamal Abdic has been brought in for questioning on the disappearance
Dialogue: 0,0:47:24.54,0:47:27.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}…居民梅根 · 希普韋爾的失蹤一事{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}of Ardsley-on-Hudson resident, Megan Hipwell.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:27.89,0:47:32.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}根據消息來源，他是希普韋爾太太的心理醫生…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}He was, according to sources, Mrs. Hipwell's psychiatrist...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.58,0:47:38.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}幾年以來，我第一次有了目標{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}For the first time in ages I have purpose.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.55,0:47:44.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}或至少我有了分心的事…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Or at least, I have a distraction...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:45.56,0:47:49.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我希望梅根會平安無事地現身，真的{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I want Megan to show up safe and sound. I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:52.55,0:47:54.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,斯科特：我們需要盡快見面\N{\rENG}SCOTT: We need to meet ASAP
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.68,0:47:56.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}只是現在還不到時候{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Just not quite yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.27,0:48:05.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨\N{\rENG}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.14,0:48:09.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 怎麼了？ - 阿布迪克被放出來了\N{\rENG}- What's wrong?  - Abdic's been released.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.56,0:48:10.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,什麼？！\N{\rENG}What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.17,0:48:13.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,沒有足夠的證據\N{\rENG}There wasn't enough evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.20,0:48:17.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,因為是我讓他被抓起來的，他開口了，談了很多\N{\rENG}And because I'm the one that got him arrested, he talked. A lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:17.31,0:48:20.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,他們…他們會對他立案的，只是需要些時間\N{\rENG}They'll build a case against him, it'll just take some time.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.72,0:48:23.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,你十分確定他就是你看見的和梅根在一起的那個傢伙？\N{\rENG}Are you totally sure he's the guy you saw Megan with?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.72,0:48:24.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\rENG}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.36,0:48:29.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你最好他媽的確定  - 我不明白…\N{\rENG}- You sure as fuck better be.  - I don't understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.44,0:48:31.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 警察認為是我幹的  - 是啊，可是他是那個…\N{\rENG}- The police think I did it.  - Yeah, but he's the one...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:31.56,0:48:36.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,他告訴他們梅根很不幸，我是個妒忌心強喜歡控制的丈夫\N{\rENG}He told them Megan's miserable, that I'm a jealous, controlling husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.37,0:48:40.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我相信他們只是想把你的嫌疑排除…\N{\rENG}I'm sure that they're just trying to rule you out...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.86,0:48:42.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,阿布迪克告訴他們我打她\N{\rENG}Abdic told them I'm abusive.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:43.78,0:48:47.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,在她出走的時候，我…我也不去追她\N{\rENG}When she walked out, I didn't go after her.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.65,0:48:51.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,說我從不打電話看看她如何了\N{\rENG}I never called to check on her.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.81,0:48:56.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,說我去他媽的運動酒吧，喝得酩酊大醉\N{\rENG}I went to a sports bar, for fuck's sake, and got drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.16,0:48:59.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，我們只需要找到更多的阿布迪克的證據\N{\rENG}No. We just need to find more evidence on Abdic.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:59.38,0:49:01.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,我已經花了一整天檢查她的東西\N{\rENG}I've spent the whole day going through her stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.70,0:49:06.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,沒有電郵，什麼都沒有，沒有信件、電郵，一無所有\N{\rENG}There's no emails, there's nothing, no letters, no emails. Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.92,0:49:11.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,有那麼一瞬間，我都想親自聯繫阿布迪克了…\N{\rENG}For a second, I thought about contacting Abdic myself...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.84,0:49:16.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,媽的破電話響個不停！\N{\rENG}Fucking phone won't stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.94,0:49:20.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,我是斯科特，是…是，等一下，等一下\N{\rENG}This is Scott. Yeah. Hold on. Hold on.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.86,0:49:22.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不介意？\N{\rENG}Do you mind?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.70,0:49:51.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,你好沉啊，你好胖啊，你是個小胖紙\N{\rENG}You're heavy. You're a fatty. You're a little fatty.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.02,0:49:54.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,蕾切爾？不，安娜，進屋裏去\N{\rENG}Rachel? No. Anna, get in the house.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.14,0:50:05.67,CHS,,0,0,0,,你…你老婆星期五晚上打了我！\N{\rENG}Your wife hit me on Friday night!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.74,0:50:08.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你在說什麼呢？ - 是的，她打了，是的，她打我了\N{\rENG}- What are you talking about?  - Yes. Yes, she did. Yes, you did.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:08.95,0:50:12.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,然後她…然後她上了你的車\N{\rENG}And then she got in your car.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:12.62,0:50:15.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，她說那天晚上你衝她叫喊\N{\rENG}No. She said you yelled at her that night.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.16,0:50:16.45,CHS,,0,0,0,,不，不是那麼回事！\N{\rENG}No. That is not what happened!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.47,0:50:19.02,CHS,,0,0,0,,她…她在隧道裏，她…她打了我\N{\rENG}She was in the tunnel. And she hit me.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.19,0:50:22.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不想當街和你爭吵，現在是大白天你已經醉了\N{\rENG}I won't argue in the street. The middle of the day and you're drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.44,0:50:24.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,我沒醉，湯姆！\N{\rENG}I'm not drunk, Tom!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.57,0:50:29.47,CHS,,0,0,0,,我老婆害怕你\N{\rENG}My wife is scared of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.50,0:50:31.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,怕什麼？\N{\rENG}Of what?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.15,0:50:35.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我不知道你是開玩笑還是什麼，我們就從綁架孩子說起\N{\rENG}I don't even know if that's a joke or not. Let's start with child abduction.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.93,0:50:38.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是胡說！你知道根本…不是那麼回事\N{\rENG}That's bullshit. You know that's not... how it happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:38.70,0:50:41.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,你我都很清楚你能幹出什麼事來\N{\rENG}You and I both know what you're capable of.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:47.00,0:50:49.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,你剛去斯科特 · 希普韋爾家了？\N{\rENG}You were just at Scott Hipwell's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:52.54,0:50:55.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你為什麼去斯科特 · 希普韋爾家？ - 因為我想幫他…幫他\N{\rENG}- Why are you at Scott Hipwell's house?!  - Because I'm helping him.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.84,0:50:56.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,幫什麼？\N{\rENG}How?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.55,0:50:59.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 幫他找到梅根  - 你都不認識梅根！\N{\rENG}- To try and find Megan.  - You don't even know Megan!
Dialogue: 0,0:51:02.15,0:51:06.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,蕾切，我覺得你誰都幫不了\N{\rENG}Rach. I don't think you're helping anybody.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:09.68,0:51:13.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,那麼你來這裏是想恢復你失去的記憶\N{\rENG}So you're here because you want to uncover lost memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.43,0:51:15.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是這樣嗎？ - 你有口音\N{\rENG}- Is that correct?  - You have an accent.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.24,0:51:17.41,CHS,,0,0,0,,什麼？\N{\rENG}Pardon?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.44,0:51:20.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,不好意思，我…我沒想到你會有口音\N{\rENG}Sorry. I wasn't expecting you to have an accent.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.83,0:51:24.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,是啊，你也有口音\N{\rENG}Well, you have an accent.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.94,0:51:29.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 你從哪兒來？ - 我是美國公民\N{\rENG}- Where are you from?  - I'm an American citizen.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:29.96,0:51:32.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是我想你不是來這裏談論我的\N{\rENG}But I guess you're not here to talk about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.89,0:51:35.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 除非你真的是…  - 不…不，對不起，我只是…\N{\rENG}- Unless, you are...  - No. I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.90,0:51:37.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是想找個話題\N{\rENG}I was just trying to make conversation.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.81,0:51:41.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,暫時失憶，你經歷的是暫時性失憶\N{\rENG}The blackouts. You're experiencing blackouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.47,0:51:45.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,你想跟我聊聊你的情況嗎？\N{\rENG}Do you want to tell me about them?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:50.80,0:51:57.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,唔，我醒著的時候，當有人告訴我我做過的事時\N{\rENG}Well, when I wake up, and when someone tells me what I've done,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.21,0:52:04.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,感覺那根本不像我，我根本不會做出那樣的事\N{\rENG}it just doesn't feel like me or like something that I would do.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.58,0:52:07.29,CHS,,0,0,0,,我為此感覺很糟，但是…\N{\rENG}I feel bad about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:08.17,0:52:12.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是一切都似乎隔得那麼遙遠，彷彿我做了一個…\N{\rENG}But it's like it's so far removed that I have a...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.76,0:52:16.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,我感覺還不夠糟\N{\rENG}I just don't feel bad enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.09,0:52:18.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,你想為你的所作所為承擔起個人的責任\N{\rENG}You want to take personal responsibility for what you've done,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.94,0:52:23.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是你發現很難感到有責任，因為你甚至都不記得了\N{\rENG}but you find it difficult to feel accountable because you can't even remember it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.39,0:52:27.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,是嗎？\N{\rENG}Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.67,0:52:33.91,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 是啊  - 那麼蕾切爾，除了喜歡喝酒…\N{\rENG}- Yeah.  - So, Rachel, besides drinking...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:35.32,0:52:37.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,顯然你喝酒的吧\N{\rENG}Because you clearly drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:37.77,0:52:40.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,你今天就喝了不少酒，有沒有？\N{\rENG}You've been drinking today, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.36,0:52:49.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,你還喜歡別的什麼？有沒有任何業餘愛好？\N{\rENG}What else do you enjoy? Do you have any hobbies?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.04,0:52:54.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我喜歡畫畫，藝術，我想\N{\rENG}I like to draw. Art, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:55.27,0:52:58.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,很好，我們可以試著通過畫畫來恢復你的部分記憶\N{\rENG}Good. We can try to regain some of your memories by drawing them.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.67,0:53:00.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,我試過了，不起作用\N{\rENG}I've tried it. It doesn't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.89,0:53:05.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,你有沒有一直往前追溯到你開始大量飲酒的時候？\N{\rENG}Have you ever tracked all the way back to when you started drinking heavily?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.44,0:53:08.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是什麼時候？\N{\rENG}When was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.94,0:53:14.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,當時我還和湯姆在一起，但是我懷不上孩子\N{\rENG}It was with Tom. When I couldn't get pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.45,0:53:16.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,誰是湯姆？\N{\rENG}Who's Tom?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:16.72,0:53:18.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,他是我的前夫\N{\rENG}He's my ex-husband.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.36,0:53:21.44,CHS,,0,0,0,,你想談談那些事嗎？\N{\rENG}Do you want to talk about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.46,0:53:24.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,我真的很想要個寶寶\N{\rENG}I really wanted a baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.37,0:53:36.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,我們想盡一切辦法但都不管用\N{\rENG}We tried everything and nothing worked.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.18,0:53:42.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,這絕對地…\N{\rENG}And it just absolutely...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.14,0:53:58.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,這令我心碎\N{\rENG}It just broke my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:59.82,0:54:03.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以我傷心欲絕，然後…\N{\rENG}So I got really sad and then...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:05.71,0:54:10.10,CHS,,0,0,0,,酒精摧毀了我們\N{\rENG}The booze just broke us.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.48,0:54:12.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,對\N{\rENG}Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:13.92,0:54:15.52,CHS,,0,0,0,,接著說\N{\rENG}Tell me more.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.95,0:54:22.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,我曾經注意到一對完美夫妻\N{\rENG}I used to watch this perfect couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.49,0:54:32.08,CHS,,0,0,0,,他們簡直就是真愛的化身\N{\rENG}And they were just the embodiment of true love.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.69,0:54:35.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,那好像是你一直希望得到的那種愛\N{\rENG}It's like the kind of love you always want.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.39,0:54:42.59,CHS,,0,0,0,,可是後來，她卻背叛了他\N{\rENG}And then, she betrayed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.08,0:54:51.36,CHS,,0,0,0,,這件事觸動了我內心的什麼…\N{\rENG}And it's sparked something in me...
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.05,0:54:57.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,說實話你為什麼來這裏，蕾切爾？\N{\rENG}Why are you really here, Rachel?
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.64,0:55:01.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,因為我害怕我自己\N{\rENG}Because I'm afraid of myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.13,0:55:15.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,七月五號：一點三十三、一點三十四、一點三十七…\N{\rENG}July 5th: 1:33, 1:34, 1:37...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:15.76,0:55:22.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,她在凌晨一點三十八又打過一次，然後在下午的一點四十四、一點四十五、兩點十五多次打來\N{\rENG}She calls again 1:38 and then she calls again at 1:44, 1:45, 2:15 PM.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.36,0:55:24.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,然後是七月六號…你知道我的意思\N{\rENG}And then July 6th... You get the point.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.04,0:55:28.37,CHS,,0,0,0,,有時她一天給他發來幾十條短信\N{\rENG}She sometimes texted him dozens of times a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.44,0:55:32.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 但這些都是匿名號碼發來的  - 匿名就是蕾切爾\N{\rENG}- But these are all from an unknown number.  - Unknown is Rachel.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.59,0:55:34.31,CHS,,0,0,0,,你只有撥號的紀錄\N{\rENG}You have a log of the calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.33,0:55:37.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是沒有他們互相通話的內容的紀錄\N{\rENG}You don't have a log of what they're saying to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.14,0:55:42.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看，自從那次嬰兒事件之後，她有沒有再回過你們家？\N{\rENG}Look, has she been back to the house since the incident with your child?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.77,0:55:44.04,CHS,,0,0,0,,據我所知沒有\N{\rENG}Not that I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.07,0:55:46.65,CHS,,0,0,0,,這樣的話也許可以給你立一個二級騷擾的案子\N{\rENG}Well, then you might have a case for harassment in the second degree,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.67,0:55:49.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是這些都是短信，並不構成威脅，所以…\N{\rENG}but these are texts, they're not threats, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.07,0:55:54.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,她一直在斯科特 · 希普韋爾家周圍轉悠，非常頻繁\N{\rENG}She's been hanging around Scott Hipwell's house. A lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.94,0:55:59.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,我知道，現在存在非常多也許有意義的線索\N{\rENG}I'm aware. There are a lot of loose ends here that suggest something,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.94,0:56:02.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,但是都不能太說得通\N{\rENG}but they don't add up to much.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.04,0:56:04.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,如果你能給我提供些更加可靠的…\N{\rENG}If you can bring me something more solid...
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.24,0:56:06.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,你還需要什麼？\N{\rENG}What more do you need?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.16,0:56:08.97,CHS,,0,0,0,,證據，確鑿證據\N{\rENG}Evidence. Real evidence?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:15.25,0:56:18.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,你確定你丈夫不想與他前妻保持聯繫嗎？\N{\rENG}You sure your husband doesn't want to stay in touch with his ex-wife?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.45,0:56:21.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,什麼？不，她在騷擾我們！\N{\rENG}What? No. She's harassing us.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:21.15,0:56:22.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,他也是這麼說的？\N{\rENG}Is that what he calls it?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:06.79,0:57:08.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,嗨\N{\rENG}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.72,0:57:51.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 嗨  - 我院子裏都是記者\N{\rENG}- Hi.  - Reporters are in my yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.82,0:57:55.34,CHS,,0,0,0,,到處都是，我沒別的地方可去了\N{\rENG}Everywhere. I didn't know where else to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.52,0:57:56.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,進來吧\N{\rENG}Come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:08.34,0:58:11.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,警探剛…\N{\rENG}The detective just...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.10,0:58:17.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,警探剛告訴我長久以來我一直盼望聽到的消息\N{\rENG}The detective just told me something I've wanted to hear for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:21.80,0:58:23.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,她懷孕了\N{\rENG}She's pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.05,0:58:27.50,CHS,,0,0,0,,她告訴了她心理醫生而不是我\N{\rENG}She told her shrink but not me.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.86,0:58:33.35,CHS,,0,0,0,,我一直想要孩子\N{\rENG}I wanted a family,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:33.89,0:58:36.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,可她卻是步步與我作對\N{\rENG}but she fought me every step of the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:39.48,0:58:41.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我們總是為此爭吵\N{\rENG}We always fought about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.71,0:58:46.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,梅根有沒有向你說起過我的什麼事？\N{\rENG}Did Megan ever say anything about me to you?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.48,0:58:58.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,她愛過你\N{\rENG}She loved you.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:00.16,0:59:05.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,她愛你的方式就是人們夢寐以求的相愛方式\N{\rENG}She loved you in ways that people only dream of being loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.70,0:59:38.70,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\rZHU}{\fs60\fsp20\pos(980,600)}一個月以前
Dialogue: 0,1:00:07.04,1:00:08.74,CHS,,0,0,0,,你不該在這裏\N{\rENG}You shouldn't be here.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.54,1:00:14.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只想…\N{\rENG}I just...
Dialogue: 0,1:00:15.25,1:00:17.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,我需要告訴什麼人\N{\rENG}I need to tell someone,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.15,1:00:19.79,CHS,,0,0,0,,就一次\N{\rENG}just once.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:19.99,1:00:21.69,CHS,,0,0,0,,就是想大聲說出來\N{\rENG}Just say it out loud.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.96,1:00:25.66,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想告訴你\N{\rENG}I want to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.14,1:00:31.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,然後我就走，我發誓\N{\rENG}And then I'll be gone, I swear.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.86,1:00:41.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,那時我孕了\N{\rENG}I got pregnant.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.34,1:00:47.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,在我十七歲時\N{\rENG}I was seventeen.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.94,1:00:50.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,我自己生下了孩子\N{\rENG}I had her by myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.84,1:00:57.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,她長著黑色眼睛和金色頭髮\N{\rENG}She had dark eyes and blond hair.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.43,1:01:07.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,我以為這樣會很難，但實際並不難\N{\rENG}I expected it to be hard, but it wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.90,1:01:11.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,很容易\N{\rENG}It was easy.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:13.56,1:01:15.96,CHS,,0,0,0,,因為我愛她\N{\rENG}Because I loved her.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.45,1:01:19.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我愛她\N{\rENG}I loved her.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.67,1:01:23.57,CHS,,0,0,0,,我叫她伊麗莎白\N{\rENG}I called her Elizabeth.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.03,1:01:26.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,麗比\N{\rENG}Libby.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.55,1:01:30.20,CHS,,0,0,0,,麗比\N{\rENG}Libby.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.91,1:01:38.81,CHS,,0,0,0,,那是在十二月\N{\rENG}It was December.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.16,1:01:41.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,我們大吵了一架，我和麥克\N{\rENG}We'd gotten in a fight, me and Mac.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:44.99,1:01:47.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,他一走了之\N{\rENG}He'd gone off and left.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.14,1:01:51.32,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}屋頂正漏著雨{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}The roof was leaking.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.72,1:01:57.43,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我感到徹骨的寒冷，於是就躲進了浴缸{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I was freezing cold, so I got in the tub.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:58.93,1:02:01.61,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我把麗比帶在身邊{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I brought Libby in with me,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.91,1:02:04.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}讓她依偎在我胸前{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}put her on my chest,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.99,1:02:08.90,CHS,,0,0,0,,她的頭就在我的頦下\N{\rENG}her head just under my chin.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.76,1:02:18.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,我睡了過去\N{\rENG}I fell asleep.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.15,1:02:27.13,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我鬆開了她{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I let her go.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.37,1:02:30.07,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我鬆開了她{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I let her go.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.08,1:02:32.78,CHS,,0,0,0,,我鬆開了她\N{\rENG}I let her go.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.92,1:02:36.92,CHS,,0,0,0,,我鬆開了她\N{\rENG}I let her go.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:40.44,1:02:42.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不敢正視{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I couldn't look.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:42.75,1:02:45.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不想看到這一幕{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I didn't want to see it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:45.45,1:02:47.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我不想看到她{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I didn't want to see her.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:51.77,1:02:54.30,CHS,,0,0,0,,我把她用毯子包裹住\N{\rENG}I wrapped her in a blanket.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.73,1:02:56.93,CHS,,0,0,0,,然後掩埋了她\N{\rENG}And I buried her.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.58,1:03:14.38,CHS,,0,0,0,,後來…\N{\rENG}Then...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.42,1:03:19.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,有天晚上麥克出去了\N{\rENG}Mac went out that night.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.35,1:03:24.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,就再也沒有回來\N{\rENG}And he never came back.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.17,1:03:28.71,CHS,,0,0,0,,他再也沒有回來\N{\rENG}He never came back.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:48.28,1:03:50.68,CHS,,0,0,0,,我想念我們的家\N{\rENG}I missed our home.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:58.95,1:04:04.00,CHS,,0,0,0,,所以有一天在我喝醉後，我決定去那裏看看\N{\rENG}So one day when I was drunk, I decided to go there.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.56,1:04:12.25,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}前門是開著的，所以我並沒有闖進去{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}The front door was open. It's not like I broke in.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.32,1:04:26.95,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}然後我聽見了伊維{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}And then I heard Evie.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.99,1:04:30.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}伊維是誰？{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Who's Evie?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.79,1:04:33.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}湯姆的寶寶{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Tom's baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.51,1:04:57.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我知道這聽上去很瘋狂{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I know this sounds insane,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.45,1:05:02.06,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}但是我只是想抱抱她{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}but I just wanted to hold her.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.52,1:05:08.72,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}就抱一會兒{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Just for a moment.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.47,1:05:38.05,CHS,,0,0,0,,蕾切爾？你在幹嘛？！\N{\rENG}Rachel? What are you doing?!
Dialogue: 0,1:05:38.21,1:05:40.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,你想要幹嘛？\N{\rENG}What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.50,1:05:43.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,蕾切爾…\N{\rENG}Rachel...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:06.27,1:06:08.75,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我沒有想要傷害她{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I wasn't going to hurt her.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:10.14,1:06:12.14,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}我絕不可能傷害她{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}I would never hurt her.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.92,1:06:19.12,CHS,,0,0,0,,我只是想抱抱她\N{\rENG}I just wanted to hold her.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.48,1:06:46.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}發現部分腐爛的屍體…發現女性屍體…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Partially decomposed body found... Female body found...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.29,1:06:49.84,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}死因是強力鈍擊傷…發現部分腐爛的屍體…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Death a result of blunt force trauma. Partially decomposed body.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.87,1:06:54.51,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}梅根 · 希普韋爾…目前變成了對殺人案的調查…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Megan Hipwell. Investigation now being called a homicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:55.74,1:06:58.55,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}有消息說所發現的部分腐爛的屍體…{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Sources say the partially decomposed body found
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.61,1:07:03.11,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}…是失蹤的阿茲利女子梅根 · 希普韋爾，死因是強力鈍擊傷{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}is missing Ardsley woman Megan Hipwell. Death a result of blunt force trauma.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.27,1:07:06.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,{\i1}梅根 · 希普韋爾的失蹤目前變成了對殺人案的調查{\i0}\N{\rENG\i1}Megan Hipwell's investigation now being called a homicide.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.80,1:07:08.54,CHS,,0,0,0,,希普韋爾先生？\N{\rENG}Mr. Hipwell?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.14,1:07:52.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎麼了？\N{\rENG}What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.40,1:07:54.80,CHS,,0,0,0,,對不起\N{\rENG}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:16.34,1:08:18.40,CHS,,0,0,0,,這讓我想起以前我看著你…\N{\rENG}This reminds me of when I used to watch
Dialogue: 0,1:08:18.41,1:08:21.82,CHS,,0,0,0,,…穿戴整齊，然後再回到她身邊的情景\N{\rENG}you getting dressed before going back to her.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.29,1:08:29.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,回到這所房子裏來\N{\rENG}Back to this house.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.69,1:08:33.58,CHS,,0,0,0,,我其實挺懷念當第三者時的感覺\N{\rENG}I actually miss being the other woman.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.15,1:08:38.39,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 欺騙蕾切爾有沒有讓你很享受？ - 這算什麼問題？\N{\rENG}- Did you enjoy cheating on Rachel?  - Seriously?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.99,1:08:42.15,CHS,,0,0,0,,我們能不能別受她擺佈？\N{\rENG}Can we not fixate on her?!
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.61,1:08:47.24,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 我今天又看見她了  - 在哪兒？\N{\rENG}- I saw her again today.  - Where?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.31,1:08:51.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,今天下午當警察帶斯科特回家時，她就在街對面\N{\rENG}This afternoon when the police brought Scott back home. She was across the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:55.09,1:08:57.98,CHS,,0,0,0,,她看見我時變得具有攻擊性\N{\rENG}And when she saw me she got aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.17,1:08:59.87,CHS,,0,0,0,,怎麼個攻擊性？\N{\rENG}Aggressive how?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.97,1:09:02.17,CHS,,0,0,0,,要是蕾切爾殺了梅根呢？\N{\rENG}What if Rachel killed Megan?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:02.26,1:09:04.48,CHS,,0,0,0,,蕾切爾沒殺梅根\N{\rENG}Rachel did not kill Megan.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:04.58,1:09:06.46,CHS,,0,0,0,,那她為什麼偷偷摸摸地圍著斯科特家轉？\N{\rENG}Then why is she creeping around Scott's house?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.48,1:09:10.01,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 她很危險這你知道  - 安娜，親愛的\N{\rENG}- She's dangerous and you know it.  - Anna, sweetheart,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.03,1:09:12.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,蕾切爾很傷心\N{\rENG}Rachel is a sad person.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.69,1:09:14.99,CHS,,0,0,0,,她完全是無害的\N{\rENG}She's completely harmless.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.80,1:09:45.42,CHS,,0,0,0,,你在這裏幹嘛？你…你怎麼進來的？\N{\rENG}What are you doing here? How did you get in?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:49.83,1:09:51.33,CHS,,0,0,0,,過來\N{\rENG}Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:52.06,1:09:54.26,CHS,,0,0,0,,和我共飲啤酒\N{\rENG}Have a beer with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.76,1:09:56.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,我…我現在不想喝\N{\rENG}I'm not drinking right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.26,1:10:04.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,萊利警探昨晚來看我\N{\rENG}Detective Riley came to see me last night.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.55,1:10:09.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,檢驗結果我不是父親\N{\rENG}It turns out I'm not the father.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.46,1:10:12.53,CHS,,0,0,0,,心理醫生也不是\N{\rENG}Neither is the shrink.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:14.64,1:10:17.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,我老婆有沒有向你袒露過還有第三個男人？\N{\rENG}Did my wife confide in you about a third man?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.10,1:10:22.64,CHS,,0,0,0,,坐下\N{\rENG}Sit down.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.26,1:10:27.86,CHS,,0,0,0,,坐下！\N{\rENG}Sit down!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.09,1:10:34.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,你看，我不知道…我不知道這是怎麼…\N{\rENG}Look, I don't know what this is about...
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.21,1:10:38.27,CHS,,0,0,0,,噢，拜託！你和梅根不是要好朋友嗎？\N{\rENG}Come on! You and Megan were such good friends.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:39.59,1:10:41.49,CHS,,0,0,0,,你一定是知道的\N{\rENG}You must have known.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:43.67,1:10:46.76,CHS,,0,0,0,,- 承認吧  - 承認什麼？\N{\rENG}- Admit it.  - Admit what?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.85,1:10:49.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,承認你從沒他媽的遇見過我老婆！\N{\rENG}Admit that you never even fucking met my wife!
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.93,1:10:56.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,警探說你甚至不認識梅根\N{\rENG}The Detective said you didn't even know Megan.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.55,1:11:00.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,她也用了些其他的詞\N{\rENG}She used other words too.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.49,1:11:04.60,CHS,,0,0,0,,酒癮，也許甚至精神不穩定？\N{\rENG}Alcoholic. Maybe even mentally unstable?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.83,1:11:08.03,CHS,,0,0,0,,對不起，我真的只是想幫你\N{\rENG}I am sorry. I was honestly just trying to help.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.44,1:11:10.73,CHS,,0,0,0,,你是湯姆的瘋子前妻！\N{\rENG}You're Tom's crazy ex!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.35,1:11:13.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,你他媽的打算何時告訴我這一點，哈？\N{\rENG}When the fuck were you going to tell me that?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.93,1:11:17.62,CHS,,0,0,0,,現在警探甚至問我是否你和我搞在一起了？！\N{\rENG}And now the detective is asking if you and I are in a relationship?!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:17.81,1:11:22.19,CHS,,0,0,0,,你？！打死我都不會喜歡像你這樣的人！\N{\rENG}You?! I would never even get near someone like you!
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.79,1:11:26.63,CHS,,0,0,0,,我老婆死了，而你卻在對我撒謊！？\N{\rENG}My wife is dead, and you're lying to me!?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.19,1:11:30.77,CHS,,0,0,0,,你這人哪有毛病？誰會做這樣的事？\N{\rENG}What's wrong with you? Who does this?
